NAME
    gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories - manage Cloud Build Artifacts
        repositories

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories COMMAND [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity.

    Run $ gcloud help for details.

COMMANDS
    COMMAND is one of the following:

     add-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Add an IAM policy binding to the IAM policy of a Cloud Build
        Artifacts repository.

     create
        (ALPHA) Create a Cloud Build Artifacts repository.

     delete
        (ALPHA) Delete a Cloud Build Artifacts repository.

     get-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Get IAM policy for a Cloud Build Artifacts repository.

     list
        (ALPHA) List Cloud Build Artifacts repositories.

     remove-iam-policy-binding
        (ALPHA) Remove an IAM policy binding from the IAM policy of a Cloud
        Build Artifacts repository.

     set-iam-policy
        (ALPHA) Set the IAM policy for a Cloud Build Artifacts repository.

EXAMPLES
    To create a repository with the name my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories create my-repo

    To delete a repository with the name my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories delete my-repo

    To list all Cloud Build Artifacts repositories, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories list

    To set an IAM policy for repository my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories set-iam-policy my-repo \
            policy.json

    To get an IAM policy for repository my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories get-iam-policy my-repo

    To add an IAM policy binding for the role of 'roles/editor' for the user
    'test-user@gmail.com' on repository my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories add-iam-policy-binding \
            my-repo
        --member='user:test-user@gmail.com' --role='roles/editor'

    To remove an IAM policy binding for the role of 'roles/editor' for the user
    'test-user@gmail.com' on repository my-repo, run:

        $ gcloud alpha build-artifacts repositories \
            remove-iam-policy-binding my-repo
        --member='user:test-user@gmail.com' --role='roles/editor'

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. If this
    command fails with API permission errors despite specifying the right
    project, you may be trying to access an API with an invitation-only early
    access whitelist.

